stimulating hormone","Vasopressin"],"correctOptions":[0],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe anterior pituitary (adenohypophysis) produces six major hormones: \u003Cstrong\u003Egrowth hormone\u003C/strong\u003E (GH), prolactin (PRL), thyroid stimulating hormone (TSH), adrenocorticotropic hormone (ACTH), follicle stimulating hormone (FSH), and luteinising hormone (LH).\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe posterior pituitary (neurohypophysis) does not produce hormones but stores and releases \u003Cstrong\u003Eantidiuretic hormone\u003C/strong\u003E (ADH, also called \u003Cstrong\u003Evasopressin\u003C/strong\u003E) and \u003Cstrong\u003Eoxytocin\u003C/strong\u003E, which are produced in the hypothalamus.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMelanocyte stimulating hormone\u003C/strong\u003E is produced by the intermediate lobe of the pituitary\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["The anterior pituitary produces growth hormone, prolactin, thyroid stimulating hormone, adrenocorticotropic hormone, follicle stimulating hormone, and luteinising hormone","The posterior pituitary stores and releases antidiuretic hormone and oxytocin, but does not produce them"],"references":["Hormone supply to the pituitary gland: A comprehensive investigation of female\u2011related tumors (Review). Int J Mol Med. 2022 Oct;50(4):122. doi: 10.3892/ijmm.2022.5178. Epub 2022 Aug 10. PMID: 35946461; PMCID: PMC9387558.","Melmed, S., Polonsky, K. S., Larsen, P. R., \u0026 Kronenberg, H. M. (2015). Williams textbook of endocrinology E-Book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Clark, O. H., Duh, Q. Y., Kebebew, E., Gosnell, J. E., \u0026 Shen, W. T. (Eds.). (2016). Textbook of endocrine surgery. JP Medical Ltd","Young, W. F. (2011). Netter\u0027s Endocrine System: Netter Collection of Medical Illustrations: Endocrine System E-book. Elsevier Health Sciences","Wass, J. A., \u0026 Stewart, P. M. (Eds.). (2011). Oxford textbook of endocrinology and diabetes.